> so.. how can tails specific metadata survive through all
> three steps?

You're confusing filesystem metadata (such as file ownership) that
lives in inodes in the filesystem, with file metadata (such as GPS
coordinates) that live inside the file itself.

The former generally does not survive the process you're describing.
The later survives it pretty well.

